# app/views/admin_mailer/password_theft_alert.text.erb
🚨 CRITICAL SECURITY ALERT
Password Theft Detected

======================
COMPROMISED CREDENTIALS
======================
Username: <%= @username %>
Client ID: <%= @client.id %>
Status: LOCKED
Locked at: <%= @client.locked_at&.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S UTC') || 'Just now' %>

======================
USER INFORMATION
======================
<% if @user %>
Email: <%= @user.email %>
User ID: <%= @user.id %>
Device: <%= @device.name %> (<%= @device.platform %>)
<% else %>
No user associated (preallocated client)
<% end %>

======================
SUSPICIOUS ACTIVITY
======================
Password used simultaneously from <%= @geolocations.size %> different locations:

<% @geolocations.each_with_index do |geo, index| %>
Location <%= index + 1 %>:
  IP: <%= geo[:ip] %>
  City: <%= geo[:geo][:city] %>
  Country: <%= geo[:geo][:country] %> (<%= geo[:geo][:country_code] %>)

<% end %>

⚠️ This is physically impossible! The same password was used from
<%= @geolocations.map { |g| g[:geo][:country] }.uniq.join(' and ') %> at the same time.

======================
ACTIONS TAKEN
======================
✅ All connections using <%= @username %> terminated
✅ Client <%= @username %> locked
✅ Password no longer valid

======================
NEXT STEPS
======================
<% if @user %>
1. Contact user: <%= @user.email %>
2. Investigate: legitimate travel or credential theft?
3. If legitimate: unlock and advise about multi-country usage
4. If theft: keep locked, issue new credentials
<% else %>
1. Preallocated client - not assigned to user yet
2. Keep locked until manually unlocked
3. Consider regenerating credential
<% end %>

---
Time: <%= Time.current.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S UTC') %>
System: ClashApiMonitorJob (Vulcain VPN)
---
